## UiSystem-D3 SpecsView Layout Refactor
**Status:** implemented
**Module:** `frontend/src/views/SpecsView.vue`
**Tags:** stack:frontend
**Depends on:** UiSystem-D1, Specs-G11

### Problem

The original `SpecsView` layout had several UX issues:
- Search input consumed vertical sidebar space that could be used for module navigation
- Breadcrumb was centered in the title bar, pushing action buttons to the far right
- The "Overview" was a separate mode with no clear visual hierarchy alongside module sections
- No way to discover a module's high-level purpose without opening its individual spec items

### Solution

Refactor the layout into a three-zone information architecture:

#### 1. Sidebar Zone (220px, scrollable)

```
[Search input]
[Overview tab]
[Category filter]
[Stack filter]
[Module filter]
```

```
[Overview — flat top-level item]
[Module accordion tree]
  ├─ Module A
  │   ├─ Outline
  │   ├─ Goals (N)
  │   └─ ...
  └─ Module B
[Stack filter drawer]
```

Changes:
- Removed search input (relocated to title bar)
- Removed Category filter (redundant; categories are now children of modules)
- Removed Module filter (redundant; modules are the accordion headers themselves)
- Added flat "Overview" item at top
- Added "Outline" as first child of every module

#### 2. Title Bar Zone (48px, fixed)

```
[Toggle]        [Breadcrumb — centered]        [Drift] [Links]
```

```
[Toggle] [Breadcrumb — left-aligned] [Search] [Drift] [Links]
```

Changes:
- Breadcrumb moved to left side (`Project / module / Section`)
- Search input (`max-width: 240px`) inserted between breadcrumb and action buttons
- Action buttons remain right-aligned

#### 3. Content Zone (flex, scrollable)

Three mutually exclusive render paths:

| Path | Trigger | Component |
|---|---|---|
| **Project Overview** | `showOverview === true` | `<MarkdownContent :content="overviewContent" />` |
| **Module Outline** | `activeModuleOutline !== null` | `<MarkdownContent :content="moduleOutlineContent" />` |
| **Module Section** | `currentSection !== null` | Category-specific renderer (GoalsTable, ArchitectureCards, etc.) |

### Responsive Behavior

- **Desktop (≥1280px)**: Full 3-zone layout as described
- **Tablet (768–1279px)**: Sidebar collapses to toggle; breadcrumb truncates with ellipsis
- **Mobile (<768px)**: Sidebar becomes fixed overlay; search shrinks to icon-only

### CSS Changes

Key style additions:
```css
.header-left {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 0.75rem;
  flex: 1;
  min-width: 0;
}

.header-search {
  max-width: 240px;
  flex-shrink: 0;
}

.outline-nav-item .section-top {
  gap: 0.4rem;
  justify-content: flex-start;
}
```

Removed styles:
- `.module-search` (sidebar search container)
- `.header-center` (absolute-centered breadcrumb)

### Requirements

- Overview must be the default view when `SpecsView` is first opened
- Module accordion must expand at least the first module by default (if no overview is active)
- Search must filter both module names and category type titles
- Active state must be visually distinct for all three view paths (blue left border)

## UiSystem-D4 i18n Integration Design for 6 Vue Views
**Status:** draft
**Module:** ui-system
**Tags:** stack:frontend
**Depends on:** UiSystem-A4

## UiSystem-D4 i18n Integration Design for 6 Vue Views
**Status:** draft
**Module:** `frontend/src/views/`, `frontend/src/i18n/`
**Tags:** stack:frontend
**Depends on:** UiSystem-A4

### Overview

Mechanical replacement of all hardcoded English strings in 6 Vue views with `t()` calls. Two categories: **completion** (ChatsView, WikiView — partially done) and **new integration** (AgentsConfigView, ProfessionsView, SkillsView, ApiSourcesView — fully hardcoded).

### Implementation Pattern

Every view follows the same 3-step pattern:

```vue
<script setup lang="ts">
import { useI18n } from 'vue-i18n'
const { t } = useI18n()
// ...existing composable imports...
</script>

<template>
  <!-- Before: -->
  <h2>Agent Forge</h2>
  <p>Loading agents...</p>

  <!-- After: -->
  <h2>{{ t('agents.title') }}</h2>
  <p>{{ t('agents.loading') }}</p>
</template>
```

### State Machine (per view)

```mermaid
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> Audit: identify hardcoded strings
    Audit --> AddKeys: add keys to en.json/zh.json
    AddKeys --> ReplaceTemplate: replace strings in template
    ReplaceTemplate --> ReplaceScript: replace strings in script
    ReplaceScript --> Verify: run dev server
    Verify --> [*]: all strings translated
```

### Data Flow

```
[en.json / zh.json] → [vue-i18n plugin] → [useI18n().t()] → [template renders]
```

### Per-View Changes

---

#### 1. ChatsView.vue — Completion (1 string)

**File**: `frontend/src/views/ChatsView.vue` (2566 lines)

Only 1 remaining hardcoded string — the system welcome message:

```vue
<!-- BEFORE: -->
<span>Hi! I'm <strong>{{ assistantName }}</strong>, your AI coding assistant. I'm glad to help you build your next great project!</span>

<!-- AFTER: -->
<span v-html="t('chat.welcome', { name: assistantName })" />
```

Note: Must use `v-html` because the English string contains `<strong>` tags. The `assistantName` is trusted (derived from AgentConfig), so `v-html` is safe here.

**Translation keys to add**:

| Key | en.json | zh.json |
|-----|---------|---------|
| `chat.welcome` | `"Hi! I'm <strong>{name}</strong>, your AI coding assistant. I'm glad to help you build your next great project!"` | `"嗨！我是 <strong>{name}</strong>，您的 AI 编程助手。很高兴帮助您构建下一个伟大的项目！"` |

---

#### 2. WikiView.vue — Completion (~20 strings)

**File**: `frontend/src/views/WikiView.vue` (864 lines)

Already uses `t('wiki.title')`, `t('wiki.raw')`, `t('wiki.newPage')`, `t('wiki.newFolder')` in sidebar. Remaining hardcoded strings in content area:

```vue
<!-- BEFORE: -->
<button title="Toggle sidebar">
<button title="Show sidebar">
<h3>Editing: {{ activePage?.title }}</h3>
<h3>New Page</h3>
<h3>New Folder</h3>
<input placeholder="Search pages..." />
<button title="Edit page">Edit</button>
<button title="Delete page">
<button title="Delete file">
<p>Select a page or file from the sidebar</p>
<span class="loading">Loading...</span>
<span>No pages yet</span>
<label>Path</label> / <label>Title</label> / <label>Source Type</label>
<option value="manual">Manual</option> / <option value="guide">Guide</option>

<!-- AFTER: -->
<button :title="t('wiki.toggleSidebar')">
<button :title="t('wiki.showSidebar')">
<h3>{{ t('wiki.editing') }} {{ activePage?.title }}</h3>
<h3>{{ t('wiki.newPageTitle') }}</h3>
<h3>{{ t('wiki.newFolderTitle') }}</h3>
<input :placeholder="t('wiki.searchPlaceholder')" />
<button :title="t('wiki.editPage')">{{ t('common.edit') }}</button>
<button :title="t('wiki.deletePage')">
<button :title="t('wiki.deleteFile')">
<p>{{ t('wiki.emptyState') }}</p>
<span class="loading">{{ t('common.loading') }}</span>
<span>{{ t('wiki.noPages') }}</span>
<label>{{ t('wiki.path') }}</label> / <label>{{ t('wiki.pageTitle') }}</label>
<option value="manual">{{ t('wiki.sourceManual') }}</option>
```

