#### 6. ApiSourcesView.vue — New Integration (~40 strings)

**File**: `frontend/src/views/ApiSourcesView.vue` (887 lines)

Must add `import { useI18n } from 'vue-i18n'` and `const { t } = useI18n()`.

```vue
<!-- BEFORE: -->
<h2>API Sources</h2>
<button title="Add API Source">
<div class="sidebar-empty">Loading...</div>
<p>No API sources configured.</p>
<button>Scan for Configs</button>
<button>Add Manually</button>
<div class="source-name">{{ source.name || '(New Source)' }}</div>
{{ source.models.length }} models
<h3>{{ isNew ? 'New API Source' : editing.name }}</h3>
<button>Test Connection</button>
<button>Save</button> / <button>Cancel</button>
<label>Provider</label> / <label>Name</label> / <label>API Key</label>
<option>Anthropic (Claude)</option> / <option>OpenAI (GPT)</option> / <option>Local / Ollama</option>
<label>API Key Env Var <span class="optional">(optional)</span></label>
<label>Base URL</label>
<label>Models</label>
<span class="col-id">Model ID</span> / <span class="col-name">Display Name</span> / <span class="col-tier">Tier</span>
<button>Add Model</button>
<span>Missing tier(s): {{ missingTiers.join(', ') }}</span>
